[30;1m12054 | [0m[35m        4) This is an alternative to the angles-based method, via the ERFA[0m
[30;1m12055 | [0m[35m           function eraFw2xy and as used in eraXys06a for example.  The two[0m
[30;1m12056 | [0m[35m           methods agree at the 1 microarcsecond level (at present), a[0m

[30;1m4144 | [0m[35m        5)  UT1-UTC is tabulated in IERS bulletins.  It increases by exactly[0m
[30;1m4145 | [0m[35m            one second at the end of each positive UTC leap second,[0m
[30;1m4146 | [0m[35m            introduced in order to keep UT1-UTC within +/- 0.9s.  n.b. This[0m
[30;1m4147 | [0m[35m            practice is under review, and in the future UT1-UTC may grow[0m
[30;1m4148 | [0m[35m            essentially without limit.[0m
